@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - wlms/ManagedInstance
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
[*] --> observe : reconcile
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE, INACTIVE
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE,\nINACTIVE
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\nconfiguration
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: wlms
slug: managedinstance
kind: ManagedInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: updating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
follow-up: create=none; update=next reconcile
GetManagedInstance confirmation; delete=none
supported drift: configuration
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, displayName, id, pluginStatus
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_wlms_managed_instances filters
compartmentId, displayName, id, pluginStatus;
exact id or exact compartmentId plus displayName
plus optional pluginStatus unique match;
duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
WLMS does not expose CreateManagedInstance or
DeleteManagedInstance in v65.110.0, so the
published runtime is bind/manage-existing only.
Successful UpdateManagedInstance responses
already return a ManagedInstance body. The
runtime uses that body plus one bounded
GetManagedInstance confirmation pass on the next
reconcile instead of inventing lifecycle or
work-request polling.
Delete is Kubernetes-local unbind only because
the SDK exposes no delete helper and no
cloud-side delete lifecycle for this family.
Plugin status remains a projected observed-state
field and optional bind filter, not a
controller-owned async lifecycle.
end note
@enduml
